{
  "texts": [
    "Estimating skydome lighting from images is challenging for restoring accurate sun behavior.",
    "To achieve this, we propose a novel residual connection from the estimated peak intensity to the HDR reconstruction to address over-smoothing output.",
    "Further, we adopt a selfattention mechanism to fuse multi-camera inputs, capturing complementary visual cues.Here we employ a two-stage process.",
    "In the first stage, we train an autoencoder to reconstruct the corresponding HDR panorama from an LDR panorama.",
    "Following [68], the encoder transforms the LDR skydome panorama into three intermediate vectors, including the peak direction vector f dir ∈ R 3, the intensity vector f int ∈ R 3 +, and the sky content vector f content ∈ R 64."
  ]
}